<HEAD>Five Killed In Train Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger train hit a freight train
that was waiting at a rail station in northern Bangladesh, killing
at least five people and injuring 50, police said today.
   Three passenger coaches and one freight car were derailed in the
crash Friday at Azimnagar station near Ishwardi, 65 miles north of
Dhaka.
   Three of the injured were in critical condition, according to
police contacted by telephone in Ishwardi. They spoke on condition
of anonymity.
   Railroad sources in Dhaka, also speaking on condition of
anonymity, said the passenger train's engineer and two linesmen
were suspended pending an investigation.
