<1ST_LINE>d a PM-KhanJewelry     05-14 0169</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Khan Jewelry,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Record Price Paid for Pearl</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A smooth, oblong pearl about the size of a quail
egg brought a record $864,286 at a benefit auction of jewelry from
the collection of the late Aga Khan.
   That was the most ever paid for a pearl, Christie's spokeswoman
Anne Young said Friday.
   The pearl, called ``La Regente,'' has been owned by Napoleon II,
Napoleon III and Princess Youssopof of Russia. The buyer, a Kuwaiti
banker, was not identified.
   Sir Sultan Mohamed Shah Aga Khan III was the 48th Imam of the
Ismailian sect of the Moslem religion for 72 years, until his death
in 1957. He was the father of Aly Khan who married actress Rita
Hayworth.
   The jewels, donated for sale by Prince Sadruddin Aga Khan,
brought $3,315,714 for the benefit of the Bellerive Foundation,
which promotes the conservation of natural resources.
   A 33.13 carat, pear-shaped diamond, also from the collection,
sold for $1.8 million to a private collector whose name was
withheld.
</TEXT>
