<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Smallest Sub,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>World's Smallest Nuclear Sub Launched</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHERBOURG, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   France on Saturday launched the world's
smallest nuclear-powered attack submarine.
   Canadian government and military officials joined French
dignitaries to watch the launching of the Amethyste, which will be
operational in 1991. Canada is considering buying the submarine.
   The manufacturers, Cherbourg Arsenal, said it is the world's
smallest nuclear-powered vessel. It is 243 feet long and 23 feet
wide and weighs 2,400 tons.
   The Amethyste has a speed of at least 25 mph and can operate at
depths up to 984 feet. It carries a crew of 66.
   The manufacturers said the submarine carries torpedoes and
anti-ship Exocet missiles.
   The Canadians have said they plan to use submarines of this type
to patrol vast areas in the Arctic.
</TEXT>
