<1ST_LINE>r i AM-GoldenStomach     05-14 0150</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Golden Stomach,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Tries To Smuggle Gold in Stomach</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOMBAY, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who tried to smuggle gold into India
by swallowing 48 nuggets was caught when an airport metal detector
started beeping, customs officials said Saturday.
   Mohammed Soorya, 30, was arrested Friday at Bombay's airport
after he arrived from the Persian Gulf emirate of Dubai, said
assistant customs collector P.J.R. Shekhar.
   A magistrate ordered Soorya to undergo a medical examination,
and an X-ray showed 48 small objects in his stomach, Shekhar said.
   He said Soorya admitted swallowing 24 ounces of gold. India bans
gold imports by private citizens.
   Soorya was being given laxatives at a a hospital, and six gold
pieces had been recovered by Saturday.
   The recovery was slow because Soorya, a Moslem, was observing
the dawn-to-dusk fast during the Islamic holy month of Ramadan and
would not swallow anything before sundown, said doctors.
</TEXT>
