<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BusRollover     05-14 0243</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Bus Rollover,0248</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bus Driver Chasing Rock-Throwing Youths, Witnesses Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus driver apparently was chasing two
youngsters who had thrown rocks at her bus when it collided with a
truck, killing one man and injuring at least nine children,
witnesses said.
   Many of the children aboard the bus said driver Patsy Windom,
34, was chasing two youths who fled in a car after throwing rocks
at the bus. The bus ignored a yield sign just before colliding with
the truck, witnesses said.
   Arthur Moreno, 24, driver of the truck, was crushed when the bus
rolled over and came to rest atop the truck. The truck was knocked
about 30 feet by the impact, tearing a fire hydrant out of the
ground.
   Nine-month-old David Lawrence Moreno, Moreno's son and only
passenger, was pulled from the mangled truck with minor injuries,
saved by his child-safety seat.
   Ms. Windom, a bus driver for 12 years, and eight children were
taken to hospitals, all with relatively minor injuries, Emergency
Medical Services Director Paul Pepe said.
   Police investigator W.T. Johnson said officers have talked to a
woman who was driving the car in which the two youths drove away
after the rock-throwing incident. The woman said the youths had
been throwing rocks at each other and one hit the bus, he said.
   The officer said investigators had not yet talked to the
youngsters or the bus driver, and no charges were filed.
</TEXT>
