<HEAD>One Woman Killed And Another Injured While Camping</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Wight is cq.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>GETTYSBURG, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman shot two female campers, one
fatally, in a desolate area near the Appalachian trail, state
police said Saturday.
   Rebecca Wight, 29, of Blackburg, Va., was killed Friday night at
a remote camping site and Claudia Brenner, 31, of Ithaca, N.Y., was
shot once in the face, state police dispatcher Clifford Whitmoyer
said.
   Whitmoyer said the women were hikers on the Appalachian trail
and had set up camp in the Michaux State Forest. He said the man
appeared at the site, pointed a gun at the women and shot and
killed Ms. Wight. Investigators had not determined a motive, he
said.
   Ms. Brenner, though wounded, made her way to Hershey Medical
Center, where nursing manager Kathy Cerullo-Frick said no
information was available Saturday on her condition.
